efferens : Maximus himself pronounced in the forum the laudatio funebris upon his son, cf. Plut. Fab. ²4 τὸ δ’ ἐγκώμιον... αὐτὸς εἶπε καταστὰς ἐν ἀγορᾷ καὶ ’γράψας τὸν λόγον ἐξέδωκεν. Cicero, Fam. iv 6, in acknowledging Sulpicius' letter of condolence upon the death of Tullia, cites the instanees of Maximus, Paulus, Gallus and Cato, all of which he also used in his Consolatio; see below.
